    <h1>UNO Game Modes — Classic, No Mercy &amp; Custom</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Three ways to play free UNO online. Pick a preset or build your own ruleset.</p>

    <h2>🎴 Classic Mode</h2>
    <p>Official UNO rules with no modifications. When a +2 or +4 is played, the next player draws immediately — no stacking, no surprises. The way UNO was designed to be played; perfect for beginners, purists, and quick games.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>2–20 players (double deck for 11+)</li>
      <li>Standard rules only — house rules are locked off</li>
      <li>First player to empty their hand wins</li>
      <li>Adjustable turn timer and starting hand size</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="/play" class="btn btn-outline-sm">Play Classic Mode</a>

    <h2>💀 No Mercy Mode</h2>
    <p>The brutal fan-favorite. Every kind of stacking is always on — +2s, +4s, and our exclusive Wild +8s pile into monster penalties. Wild Shuffle Hands cards scramble everyone's cards, illegal +4s can be challenged, and any player who collects <strong>25 cards is eliminated</strong>. The last player standing wins.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Full stacking: +2 on +2, +4 on +4, and mixed piles</li>
      <li>Wild +8 and Wild Shuffle Hands cards in the deck</li>
      <li>Wild Challenge: call out illegal +4s</li>
      <li>Elimination at 25 cards — survival is victory</li>
      <li>Optional: Skip Dodge, Reverse Bounce, Seven-Zero</li>
    </ul>
    <p><a href="/uno-no-mercy">Read the full No Mercy guide →</a></p>
    <a href="/play" class="btn btn-outline-sm">Play No Mercy</a>

    <h2>🛠️ Custom Mode</h2>
    <p>Your table, your rules. The host toggles every rule individually — the same house rules families argue about, all built in:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Stacking</strong> — +2, +4, mixed, Skip Dodge, Reverse Bounce (<a href="/rules/stacking">how stacking works</a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Seven-Zero</strong> — 7 swaps hands, 0 rotates every hand</li>
      <li><strong>Jump-In</strong> — slam an identical card out of turn</li>
      <li><strong>Draw to Match</strong> — keep drawing until you can play</li>
      <li><strong>Force Play</strong> — you must play if you can</li>
      <li><strong>Wild Challenge</strong> — bluff-check the +4s</li>
      <li><strong>Play for Places</strong> — first out wins, everyone else plays on for 2nd, 3rd…</li>
      <li><strong>Elimination</strong> — card-cap knockouts, adjustable limit</li>
      <li><strong>Extra cards</strong> — Wild +8 and Shuffle Hands toggles</li>
      <li><strong>Table settings</strong> — starting cards, turn timer, UNO grace time, room size</li>
    </ul>
    <p><a href="/house-rules">Every house rule explained →</a></p>
    <a href="/play" class="btn btn-outline-sm">Build a Custom Game</a>

    <h2>Which Mode Should You Pick?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>New to UNO or short on time?</strong> Classic — fast, fair, familiar.</li>
      <li><strong>Want drama?</strong> No Mercy — one tap turns on every brutal rule at once.</li>
      <li><strong>Playing with your family's rules?</strong> Custom — recreate exactly how your table plays.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Every mode is free, supports 2–20 players, works on any device, and needs no download or signup. The host can switch modes between rounds without remaking the room.</p>

    <div class="cta-banner">
      <h3>Ready to Play?</h3>
      <p>Pick a mode and start a game with friends — or add bots and start right now.</p>
      <a href="/play" class="btn btn-hero">Play Now</a>
    </div>
